name: Capability
description: The ability to achieve a desired effect under specified standards and conditions.

name: Function
description: Describes what a system must do.

name: Service
description: A unit of functionality packaged for use by other entities.

name: Resource
description: A logical or physical asset used by capabilities or services.

name: Operational Activity
description: Tasks or processes conducted in support of a mission.

name: Information Element
description: Information required or produced by activities.

name: Organization
description: An entity responsible for carrying out activities.

name: System
description: A set of related components that produce results.

name: Standard
description: Rules or guidelines used to ensure consistency and quality.
